The 2020 State of the Nation Address (SONA) will be delivered by President  Cyril Ramaphosa on Thursday, 13 February 2020. The SONA is an annual joint sitting of the National Assembly and National Council of Provinces. It   provide an overview of current developments in the country and  sets out government’s key plans for the year ahead. Job creation,  growing the economy and fighting gender-based violence are set to top President Cyril Ramaphosa’s 2020 State of the Nation Address.    